messages.content: i am getting unironically worried by this point
and a few things i read suggested its down to a coinflip
i need to force power off my pc and one of 2 things can happen
A. it starts back up, everything is generally okay
B. it does not start back up, signifying possible data corruption
things that would suck to lose if all my data is gon:
i can move my OS over to my ssd cause id be on a clean wipe
and my whole computer in general would be faster
Was I the only one you letted there?
had a few irl friends come and go
had one irl friend who stopped joining me like 2 years ago but he had a buncha progress
PRESSED THE POWER BUTTON I WAS SCARED AS HELL
i mean i guess im not out of the woods yet
i think its possible my account and the start-up background could stay but
my worst fear is that i had the server on when it happened
and that alone could be bad
all my desktop icons n shit are here
startup apps are doing the thing
malwarebytes is telling me to update it
we live another day lads. they are called blue screens of death for a reason
